The paper discusses the challenges of search and rescue robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed system is autonomous and requires perception and decision-making capabilities, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The system also needs to perform simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the need for communication and control, which are related to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the need for a failure-aware algorithm, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
